edlab.eda.transistorModel

Class TransistorNNModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • edlab.eda.transistorModel.TransistorNNModel

  • public class TransistorNNModel
extends java.lang.Object
    A class which can be used to model device characteristics of a transistor using a nerual network, then return outputs based on inputs passed through the trained network

        Constructor for a new TransistorNNModel
        Parameters:
        metaData - A metadata object used to return a metaData text file
        colNames - The names of the desired data columns in desired order
        transformCols - The names of the columns to be transformed (standard transform is the boxCox transform)
        numInputs - The number of input columns
        lambda - The lambda value for the boxCox transform
        learningRate - The learning rate of the NeuralNetwork
        beta1 - The beta1 learning value of the NeuralNetwork
        beta2 - The beta2 learning value of the NeuralNetwork
        batchSize - The size of batches used to train the NeuralNetwork
        numEpochs - The number of Epochs used when training the NeuralNetwork
        inputData - The input data used to train the model, given in the format of a List> Array

      • useModel

        public java.util.List<java.util.List<java.lang.String>> useModel(java.util.List<java.util.List<java.lang.String>> modelInput)
                                                          throws java.io.IOException,
                                                                 java.lang.InterruptedException
        Function to use the already fit TransistorNNModel where modelInput is the inputs, and the outputs are returned as calculated by the model The functionality in this method is also housed in the UseTransistorModel class which is more flexible as it takes a saved model, and thus retraining each time is not required when using the model
        Parameters:
        modelInput - List> Matrix of the input data for which outputs are desired
        Returns:
        a List> of outputs that correspond with the inputs to the function
